<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare">
    <body>An alias file is used to populate a header file with the information necessary for producing context-sensitive Help (CSH). In <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" />, you can open an alias file and use the Alias Editor to create and assign identifiers<MadCap:keyword term="Context-sensitive Help:identifiers;Identifiers" /> for the <MadCap:keyword term="Header files:alias files" />header file. You can use a single alias file in a project for multiple header files, or you can create a separate alias file to go with each header file.</body>
</html>